🔍 Sprint 08: Vulnerability Management & Assessment
Objective: To execute a comprehensive Vulnerability Assessment for "MegaQuagga" using industry-standard scanning tools. This project involved identifying technical weaknesses, assessing exploitability, and developing a prioritized remediation roadmap.

🛠️ Technical Workflow
Scanning & Enumeration: Executed three distinct scan types using Tenable Nessus to gather a baseline of the environment:

Basic Network Scan: Uncovered live hosts and open services.

Credentialed Patch Audit: Performed deep-system inspection for missing security patches and configuration errors.

Web Application Test: Identified vulnerabilities within web-facing assets (e.g., SQLi, XSS).

Data Interpretation & Analysis: Translated complex Nessus .nessus and .pdf reports into a structured Vulnerability Matrix, evaluating each finding based on:

CVSS Scores: Analyzing the severity of the threat.

Exploitability: Determining the likelihood of a successful attack.

Business Impact: Assessing the risk to MegaQuagga’s specific operations.

VAPT Data Visualization: Developed custom charts and graphs to communicate technical risks to non-technical stakeholders, including "Top Vulnerabilities" and "Vulnerabilities by Asset" breakdowns.

Remediation Planning: Researched and documented specific mitigation strategies for identified risks, prioritizing actions based on the "highest risk reduction for the lowest operational cost."

📄 Project Deliverables
MegaQuagga_Vulnerability_Matrix.csv: A master spreadsheet tracking vulnerabilities, risk rankings, and proposed remediations.

Executive_Vulnerability_Report.pdf: A formal report featuring data visualizations, an executive summary, and a technical deep-dive into the most critical findings.

🧰 Tools & Technologies
Scanner: Tenable Nessus (Network, Credentialed, and Web App scans).

Analysis: CVSS (Common Vulnerability Scoring System), Risk Assessment Frameworks.

Reporting: Data Visualization (Charts/Graphs), Technical Writing for Stakeholders.
